      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NO MORE TROUBLE (1) hit the ground running last time with a strong early split and tried to lead throughout but had to settle for the minors when second (22.90) at this track over 401m. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Overdue and expected to feature again. ZIPPING STROP (6) finished seventh last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 401m at this track, taking a Mix 2/3 in a quick 22.83. Top win two back and rates a key player again. MIDNIGHT STAR (2) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 340m at Bulli two runs back then prominent throughout when finishing second at this track last start. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Expected to be in this for a long way. SHE'S OUR JOY (7) must be included in calculations.",
